# High Availability — CARP, pfSync, and Firewall Redundancy

This file documents the design, configuration, and validation of a fully redundant OPNsense High Availability firewall environment using CARP Virtual IPs and pfSync state synchronization.

## Objective

Eliminate the firewall as a single point of failure by deploying an active/passive HA cluster consisting of a Master and Backup OPNsense node, with synchronized firewall states and seamless Virtual IP failover.

## Environment

| Node | Role | WAN IP | LAN IP | Sync IP |
|------|------|--------|--------|---------|
| OPNsense-Master | Active | — | 10.200.200.251/24 | 10.0.0.1 |
| OPNsense-Backup | Passive | — | 10.200.200.252/24 | 10.0.0.2 |
| CARP VIP (WAN) | Shared virtual WAN identity | 10.0.2.254/24 | — | — |
| CARP VIP (LAN) | Shared gateway for LAN clients | — | 10.200.200.254/24 | — |

